# opencode

[opencode](https://opencode.ai) is an AI coding agent built for the terminal. It provides a native TUI (Terminal User Interface) for interacting with various AI models to help with coding tasks, debugging, and more.

## Features

- **Native TUI**: A responsive, native, themeable terminal UI
- **LSP enabled**: Automatically loads the right LSPs, so the LLMs make fewer mistakes
- **Multi-session**: Start multiple agents in parallel on the same project
- **Shareable links**: Share a link to any sessions for reference or to debug
- **Claude Pro**: Log in with Anthropic to use your Claude Pro or Max account
- **Use any model**: Supports 75+ LLM providers through [Models.dev](https://models.dev), including local models

## Usage

After installing via Chocolatey, you can start using opencode by running:

```
opencode
```

Or configure authentication:

```
opencode auth login
```

For more information, visit the [official documentation](https://opencode.ai/docs/).
